    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee below\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n#### Case 1: decreasing height\n```lua\n-- vim.cmd('10new')\nvim.cmd('10new | call setline(1, range(1, 100))')\nlocal chan = vim.api.nvim_open_term(0, {})\n-- vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, table.concat(vim.fn.range(1, 100), '\\n') .. '\\n')\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, '101\\n102\\n103\\n104\\n105\\n')\n  vim.cmd('resize -2')\nend, 1000)\n```\nAfter 1 second, scrollback lines 97 and 98 are missing, while lines 92 and 93 are duplicated.\n\n#### Case 2: increasing height\n```lua\n-- vim.cmd('10new')\nvim.cmd('10new | call setline(1, range(1, 100))')\nlocal chan = vim.api.nvim_open_term(0, {})\n-- vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, table.concat(vim.fn.range(1, 100), '\\n') .. '\\n')\nvim.defer_fn(function()\n  vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, '101\\n102\\n103\\n104\\n105\\n')\n  vim.cmd('resize +2')\nend, 1000)\n```\nAfter 1 second, scrollback lines 92, 93 and 94 are misplaced: they come between lines 89 and 90 instead of 91 and 95.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe scrollback should be correct.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2260+g6b4ec2264e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot related to solving this issue\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.45.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
